cs.SI, cs.SOC, cs.CYBER, cs.DS, cs.MA 

This paper discusses the dynamics of spreading processes on graphs, specifically on the social media site Digg. It analyzes the factors that limit the final size of cascades on Digg and the mechanism for social contagion. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories are cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences). 

The paper also discusses the structure of the Digg network, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity) sub-category. Additionally, the paper uses mathematical models to analyze the spreading processes, which could place it in the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category. Finally, the paper uses statistical analysis to draw conclusions, which could place it in the cs.MA (Machine Learning) sub-category.
